# Parts List

This list contains the main mechanical and printed parts required to build the modular film scanning stand.

Quantities and lengths may depend on the final CAD model and the desired scanning height.

## Main Components

| Part | Quantity | Notes |
|---|---:|---|
| Aluminium extrusion | as needed | Cut to the desired length |
| Linear rail, 300 mm | 1 | Mini linear rail with 2 carriage blocks |
| MGN12H carriage blocks | 2 | Usually included with the rail |
| Lead screw | 1 | Length depends on the CAD model |
| Lead screw nut | 2 | for precise movement |
| Lead screw coupling | 1 | For connecting the stepper motor to the lead screw |
| Bearing for lead screw | 1 | Used in the top bearing mount |
| Stepper motor | 1 | For height adjustment and holding force |
| Camera leveling plate | 1 | For fine camera alignment |
| Panorama head / panorama plate | optional | Useful for better leveling and rotational alignment |
| Arca-Swiss quick release clamp | optional | For easier camera mounting and removal |
| Base plate | 1 | Siebdruckplatte or another stable board |
| Black acrylic sheet | optional | For laser-cut covers, panels or finishing parts |

## Fasteners and Hardware

| Part | Quantity | Notes |
|---|---:|---|
| M3 screws | as needed | Used for linear rail and smaller printed parts |
| M4 screws | as needed | Used for medium-strength printed connections |
| M5 screws | as needed | Used for adapters to aluminium extrusion |
| M5 slot nuts / T-nuts | as needed | For mounting printed adapters to the aluminium extrusion |
| M5 × 6 mm wafer head screws | as needed | Low-profile mounting screws |
| M5 × 10 mm wafer head screws | as needed | For extrusion adapters or thicker printed parts |
| M4 × 8 mm wafer head screws | as needed | For printed parts or accessory mounting |
| 3/8" camera screws | as needed | For tripod plates, leveling plates or camera accessories |
| Heat-set inserts, M3/M4/M5 | as needed | I used short threaded inserts, e.g. CNC Kitchen inserts |

## 3D Printing

| Material | Notes |
|---|---|
| PETG | Easy to print, good general choice |
| ABS / ASA | Better heat resistance, harder to print |
| Extrudr GreenTEC Pro CF | Used for this build; stiff, carbon-filled material |
| Other stiff filament | Can be used if dimensions and strength are suitable |

## Printed Parts

| Printed Part | Notes |
|---|---|
| Linear rail adapters | Connect the rail to the aluminium extrusion |
| Top bearing mount | Holds the top lead screw bearing |
| Top bearing lid | Secures the bearing in place |
| Bottom support | Lower support for the lead screw / extrusion |
| Camera carrier, first half | Mounts to the linear rail carriages |
| Camera carrier, second half | Holds the leveling plate / camera mount |
| Optional covers or spacers | Depending on the final CAD design |

## Optional Laser-Cut Parts

| Part | Material | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Side panels | Black acrylic | Optional visual or structural finishing parts |
| Covers | Black acrylic | Can be used to hide mechanics or improve appearance |
| Alignment plates | Acrylic or plywood | Optional aids for assembly and calibration |

## Notes

Check the final CAD model before ordering the lead screw, aluminium extrusion and acrylic parts.

Some screw lengths may need to be adjusted depending on the printed part thickness, insert depth and accessory stack-up.

For the base plate, a stable and flat material is recommended. A Siebdruckplatte or another rigid wooden board works well.
